Differential Equations for SC and IV PK models

# Basic IV model for PK
mod_PKPD_IV = new_ode_model(code = "
                              dAdt[1] = - (A[1]*Vm/(Km + (A[1]/V2))) - KE*A[1] - K23*A[1] + K32*A[2]
                              dAdt[2] = K23*A[1] - K32*A[2]
                              CP = A[1]/V2",
                              obs = list(cmt = 2, scale = "V2"),
                     declare_variables = c("CP"))

# Basic SC model for PK
mod_PKPD_SC = new_ode_model(code = "
                              dAdt[1] = - KA*A[1] 
                              dAdt[2] = KA*A[1] - (A[2]*Vm/(Km + (A[2]/V2))) - KE*A[2] - K23*A[2] + K32*A[3]
                              dAdt[3] = K23*A[2] - K32*A[3]
                              CP = A[2]/V2",
                              obs = list(cmt = 2, scale = "V2"),
                     declare_variables = c("CP"))

Regimen Definition for SC and IV PK models

#regimen for 1 IV dose (12mg/kg * 70kg human = 840 mg dose)
reg_PKPD_IV = new_regimen(amt = 840, time = 0)

#regimen for 1 SC 300mg dose
reg_PKPD_SC = new_regimen(amt = 300,
                   time = 0) 

#regimen for biweekly SC 300mg dose
reg_PKPD_SC_biweek = new_regimen(amt = 300,
                   times = seq(0,98,14)) 

#regimen for weekly 300mg dose
reg_PKPD_SC_week = new_regimen(amt = 300,
                   times = seq(0,98,7))

Defining Parameters for SC and IV PK models

#All values provided from Kovalenko et al. (2016)
KA = 0.261 # units of 1/d 
Vm = 1.06 # units of mg/L/d 
KE = 0.0488 # units of 1/d 
K23 = 0.104 # units of 1/d 
K32 = 0.173 # units of 1/d 
V2 = 2.60 #units of L
Km = 0.01 #units of (mg/L)

PKPDpar_IV = list(
            "Vm" = Vm,
            "KE" = KE,
            "K23" = K23,
            "K32" = K32,
            "V2" = V2,
            "Km" = Km)

PKPDpar_SC = list("KA" = KA,
            "Vm" = Vm,
            "KE" = KE,
            "K23" = K23,
            "K32" = K32,
            "V2" = V2,
            "Km" = Km)

Running PRED and IPRED PK Simulations for IV and SC models

#simulation for PK for single IV dose
simdat_PKPD_IV = sim_ode(ode = mod_PKPD_IV, 
                  regimen = reg_PKPD_IV, 
                  parameters = PKPDpar_IV, 
                  only_obs  = T , 
                  t_obs = c(seq(0, 5, 0.001), seq(5.1, 112, 0.1)), 
                  output_include = list( 
                    parameters = TRUE,
                    variables = TRUE,
                    covariates = TRUE)
                  )

#IPRED simulation for PK for single IV dose
simdat_PKPD_IV1 = sim_ode(ode = mod_PKPD_IV, 
                  regimen = reg_PKPD_IV, 
                  parameters = PKPDpar_IV, 
                  only_obs  = T , 
                  t_obs = c(seq(0, 5, 0.001), seq(5.1, 112, 0.1)), 
                  omega=cv_to_omega(par_cv=list(V2=.172, KE=0.362, KA=0.480, Vm =.195), 
                                        PKPDpar_IV),
                  output_include = list( 
                    parameters = TRUE,
                    variables = TRUE,
                    covariates = TRUE)
                  )

DATA filtration for graphing

#filter to get out CP values less than 0.01 so that they do not mess up scale of the graph at the end (values less than 0.01 are made to be 0.01)
filtered_simdat_PKPD_IV1 <- simdat_PKPD_IV1 %>%
  mutate(CP = ifelse(CP < 0.01, 0.01, CP))

filtered_simdat_PKPD_IV <- simdat_PKPD_IV %>%
  mutate(CP = ifelse(CP < 0.01, 0.01, CP))

filtered_simdat_PKPD_SC1 <- simdat_PKPD_SC1 %>%
  mutate(CP = ifelse(CP < 0.01, 0.01, CP))

filtered_simdat_PKPD_SC <- simdat_PKPD_SC %>%
  mutate(CP = ifelse(CP < 0.01, 0.01, CP))

filtered_simdat_PKPD_SC_biweek1 <- simdat_PKPD_SC_biweek1 %>%
  mutate(CP = ifelse(CP < 0.01, 0.01, CP))

filtered_simdat_PKPD_SC_biweek <- simdat_PKPD_SC_biweek %>%
  mutate(CP = ifelse(CP < 0.01, 0.01, CP))

filtered_simdat_PKPD_SC_week1 <- simdat_PKPD_SC_week1 %>%
  mutate(CP = ifelse(CP < 0.01, 0.01, CP))

filtered_simdat_PKPD_SC_week <- simdat_PKPD_SC_week %>%
  mutate(CP = ifelse(CP < 0.01, 0.01, CP))

Plot Generation for Various Dosing Regimens and Conditions

#PK Plot for 1 time SC dosing
PK_SC_sim_plot = ggplot() +
  # Add simulation data with a smooth line
  geom_line(data = filtered_simdat_PKPD_SC, aes(x = t, y = CP), size = 1.2, color = "forestgreen", linetype = "dashed") +
  geom_line(data = filtered_simdat_PKPD_SC1, aes(x = t, y = CP), size = 1.2, color = "red") +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0.08, color = "darkturquoise", size = 0.75) +
  # Set Y-axis to log scale but keep normal notation
  scale_y_log10(limits = c(0.01, 500), 
                breaks = c(0.01, 0.05, 0.1, 0.5, 1, 5, 10, 50, 100, 500),
                labels = scales::label_number()) +  # Keeps normal notation
  
  # Set X-axis from 0 to 112 with increments of 14
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(0, 112), breaks = seq(0, 112, by = 14)) +
  # Classic theme with customized gridlines
  theme_classic() +
  theme(
    panel.grid.major = element_line(color = "gray80", size = 0.5),  # Add major gridlines
    panel.grid.minor = element_line(color = "gray90", size = 0.3),  # Add minor gridlines
    axis.text = element_text(size = 14, color = "black"),
    axis.title = element_text(size = 16, face = "bold"),
    plot.title = element_text(size = 18, face = "bold", hjust = 0.5), # Center the title
    axis.line = element_line(size = 1),   # Make axis lines bolder
    axis.ticks = element_line(size = 1),
     panel.border = element_rect(color = "black", fill = NA, size = 2)# Make tick marks more visible
  ) +
  # Labels to match the given graph
  xlab("Actual Day") +
  ylab("Concentration (mg/L)") +
  ggtitle("Dose = 300mg SC")
